<item>
            <title>[PIG-2918] Avoid Spillable bag overhead where possible</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2918</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We use BagFactory.newDefaultBag() liberally, and pay a price &amp;#8211; each such bag registers with the spillable memory manager, and if we allocate a lot of tiny bags, we wind up paying for maintaining and cleaning up the internal linked list of weak references. &lt;br/&gt;
In many cases, we know a-priori that the bags are smal, and should probably be creating non-spillable bags for those cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
